commit.message:
Add project metadata to the gemspec

As per https://guides.rubygems.org/specification-reference/#metadata,
add metadata to the gemspec file. This'll allow people to more easily
access the source code, raise issues and read the changelog. These
`bug_tracker_uri`, `changelog_uri`, `documentation_uri` and
`source_code_uri` links will appear on the rubygems page at
https://rubygems.org/gems/sass-rails after the next release.

Merge pull request #398 from junaruga/feature/update-travis

Update .travis.yml

Update .travis.yml

* Update Rubies to latest version.
* Add ruby-head to Travis as allow_failures.
  * It's good to know new version Ruby's issue as faster before the release.
  * fast_finish is to get the Travis result as faster
    without waiting the result of the "allow_failures" items.
    See https://blog.travis-ci.com/2013-11-27-fast-finishing-builds/
